<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870727-0061 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Curtiss-Wright Corp.</HL><DD> 07/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CW </IN><TEXT>   Curtiss-Wright Corp. said it will post a gain of $6.2 million, or $1.27 a share, in the third quarter, reflecting a unit's sale of 103,000 acres in Nevada for $6.7 million. The unit, C-W Nevada, sold the land to Asamera Minerals Inc., a unit of Asamera Inc. of Calgary, Alberta. Under terms, C-W also gets a royalty on the future sales of smelterable metallic minerals removed from the property. Curtiss-Wright, an aerospace and defense concern based in Lyndhurst, N.J., said the gain includes a credit of $2.1 million from a tax loss carry-forward. In the year-earlier quarter, Curtiss-Wright earned $5.6 million, or $1.16 a share, on revenue of $47.5 million. </TEXT></DOC>